The Americas
------------
[8] USA (NC/NYC)
Date: Wed 11 Dec 2013
Source: The Jewish Press News Briefs [edited]
http://www.jewishpress.com/news/breaking-news/hareidim-beat-out-hare-krishna-in-measles-outbreak/2013/12/11/


Of the 175 cases of measles in the US in 2013, a mere 23 were connected to Hare Krishnas in North Carolina. The 175 cases were triple the national average in previous years. Embarrassingly enough, the largest group of people infected with measles came from our very own anti-vaccination group of Brooklyn Hareidi Jews. 30 cases of measles were diagnosed in Williamsburg, and another 28 were diagnosed in Borough Park, accounting for 1/3rd of the cases in the US in 2013. It was the largest measles outbreak in 15 years.

The original outbreak came from a London ultra-Orthodox community, which also refuses to stop endangering everyone else. An intentionally unvaccinated Hareidi teenager brought the disease back with him to the US. In July 2013, the NYC Department of Health said that that outbreak was over. But it was hardly the only case. There was a measles outbreak in these communities in 2011. And in 2010, another child brought back mumps with him from England, infecting fellow Jewish campers in upstate NY, who brought the disease home with them to Monsey and New Square, resulting in over 300 infected people.

